'''William Turakiuta Cooper''' (c.1886&ndash;4 August 1949) was a New Zealand  interpreter and land officer. Of [[Māori people|Māori]] descent, he identified with the [[Ngati Kahungunu]] [[iwi]]. He was born in [[Muriwai]], [[Gisborne Region|East Coast]], [[New Zealand]] on c.1886. His second wife was [[Whina Cooper]].<ref name="DNZB Cooper">{{DNZB|title=William Turakiuta Cooper|first= Steven|last= Oliver|id=4c34|accessdate=23 April 2017}}</ref>

